{
  "_comment": [
    "PX4 airframe identification tables for MINT. Edit this file to add or",
    "re-map airframes without touching code — airframe.py loads it at import.",
    "",
    "Source of truth: PX4-Autopilot ROMFS/px4fmu_common/init.d/airframes/",
    "CMakeLists.txt (the px4_add_romfs_files groups). Keep ranges aligned with",
    "that file when bumping the supported PX4 version.",
    "",
    "MINT supports multirotor (MULTIROTOR), fixed-wing (FIXED_WING), flying-",
    "wing/delta (DELTA_WING) and VTOL airframes only. Any SYS_AUTOSTART that",
    "matches no entry here is REJECTED (UnsupportedAirframeError) rather than",
    "coerced into a default class — coercing an out-of-scope vehicle (rover,",
    "boat, submarine, balloon, airship, helicopter, autogyro, spacecraft)",
    "would hand it advice from a control cascade it does not run.",
    "",
    "Deliberately absent (-> rejected): 2507 airship, 16000-17999 heli/",
    "autogyro, 18000-18999 balloon, 50000-52999 rover, 60000-61000 underwater,",
    "70000+ spacecraft, and the 1104 Ackermann rover sim."
  ],

